It's a hair-raising experience that is all in a day's work for the world's best surfers: riding a 42ft wave that threatens to crash down on them at any moment.

And this is the breath-taking moment that one of the thrill-seekers narrowly avoided being crushed by a gigantic wave off the coast of Portugal, where the sport's top athletes have gathered to ride massive waves in front of hundreds of spectators.

The unidentified surfer was unscathed when he made it back to the beach at the small fishing village of Nazare, where US surfer Garrett McNamara set the world record for riding the largest wave - an astonishing 98 feet - in January 2013. 

