This week, the giant waves have once again lured Mr McNamara, along with the UK's Andrew Cotton, Australia's Ross Clarke Jones and France's Benjamin Sanchis.

Mr Cotton, a former plumber from Devon, said that he expected the swells to be the largest of the year at the notorious big wave spot.

Two weeks ago the fearless surfer wiped out and was engulfed by a 60ft wave as he attempted to break the world record. He escaped with a minor arm injury.

